195 namespace nonius {
196  struct outlier_classification {
197  int samples_seen = 0;
198  int low_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR below Q1
199  int low_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR below Q1
200  int high_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR above Q3
201  int high_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR above Q3
202 
203  int total() const {
204  return low_severe + low_mild + high_mild + high_severe;
205  }
206  };
207 } // namespace nonius

285 // Invoke with a special case for void
286 
287 #define NONIUS_DETAIL_COMPLETE_INVOKE_HPP
288 
289 #include <type_traits>
290 #include <utility>
291 
292 namespace nonius {
293  namespace detail {
294  template <typename T>
295  struct complete_type { using type = T; };
296  template <>
297  struct complete_type<void> { struct type {}; };
298 
299  template <typename T>
300  using CompleteType = typename complete_type<T>::type;
301 
302  template <typename Result>
303  struct complete_invoker {
304  template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
305  static Result invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
306  return std::forward<Fun>(fun)(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
307  }
308  };
309  template <>
310  struct complete_invoker<void> {
311  template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
312  static CompleteType<void> invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
313  std::forward<Fun>(fun)(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
314  return {};
315  }
316  };
317  template <typename Sig>
318  using ResultOf = typename std::result_of<Sig>::type;
319 
320  // invoke and not return void :(
321  template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
322  CompleteType<ResultOf<Fun(Args...)>> complete_invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
323  return complete_invoker<ResultOf<Fun(Args...)>>::invoke(std::forward<Fun>(fun), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
324  }
325 
326  template <typename> struct always_true : std::true_type {};
327  struct is_callable_tester {
328  template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
329  always_true<decltype(std::declval<Fun>()(std::declval<Args>()...))> static test(int);
330  template <typename...>
331  std::false_type static test(...);
332  };
333  template <typename T>
334  struct is_callable;
335  template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
336  struct is_callable<Fun(Args...)> : decltype(is_callable_tester::test<Fun, Args...>(0)) {};
337  } // namespace detail
338 } // namespace nonius

340 namespace nonius {
341  namespace detail {
342  struct chronometer_concept {
343  virtual void start() = 0;
344  virtual void finish() = 0;
345  virtual ~chronometer_concept() = default;
346  };
347  template <typename Clock>
348  struct chronometer_model final : public chronometer_concept {
349  void start() override { started = Clock::now(); }
350  void finish() override { finished = Clock::now(); }
351 
352  TimePoint<Clock> started;
353  TimePoint<Clock> finished;
354  };
355  } // namespace detail
356 
357  struct chronometer {
358  public:
359  template <typename Fun>
360  void measure(Fun&& fun) { measure(std::forward<Fun>(fun), detail::is_callable<Fun(int)>()); }
361 
362  int runs() const { return k; }
363 
364  chronometer(detail::chronometer_concept& meter, int k)
365  : impl(&meter), k(k) {}
366 
367  private:
368  template <typename Fun>
369  void measure(Fun&& fun, std::false_type) {
370  measure([&fun](int) { fun(); });
371  }
372  template <typename Fun>
373  void measure(Fun&& fun, std::true_type) {
374  impl->start();
375  for(int i = 0; i < k; ++i) fun(i);
376  impl->finish();
377  }
378 
379  detail::chronometer_concept* impl;
380  int k;
381  };
382 } // namespace nonius

431 
432 namespace nonius {
433  namespace detail {
434  template <typename Clock = default_clock, typename Fun, typename... Args>
435  TimingOf<Clock, Fun(Args...)> measure(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
436  auto start = Clock::now();
437  auto&& r = detail::complete_invoke(fun, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
438  auto end = Clock::now();
439  auto delta = end - start;
440  return { delta, std::forward<decltype(r)>(r), 1 };
441  }
442  } // namespace detail
443 } // namespace nonius

457 // Dumb std::function implementation for consistent call overhead
458 
459 #define NONIUS_DETAIL_BENCHMARK_FUNCTION_HPP
460 
461 #include <type_traits>
462 #include <utility>
463 #include <memory>
464 
465 namespace nonius {
466  namespace detail {
467  template <typename T>
468  using Decay = typename std::decay<T>::type;
469  template <typename T, typename U>
470  struct is_related
471  : std::is_same<Decay<T>, Decay<U>> {};
472 
473  struct benchmark_function {
474  private:
475  struct concept {
476  virtual void call(chronometer meter) const = 0;
477  virtual concept* clone() const = 0;
478  virtual ~concept() = default;
479  };
480  template <typename Fun>
481  struct model : public concept {
482  model(Fun&& fun) : fun(std::move(fun)) {}
483  model(Fun const& fun) : fun(fun) {}
484 
485  model<Fun>* clone() const override { return new model<Fun>(*this); }
486 
487  void call(chronometer meter) const override {
488  call(meter, is_callable<Fun(chronometer)>());
489  }
490  void call(chronometer meter, std::true_type) const {
491  fun(meter);
492  }
493  void call(chronometer meter, std::false_type) const {
494  meter.measure(fun);
495  }
496 
497  Fun fun;
498  };
499  public:
500  template <typename Fun,
501  typename std::enable_if<!is_related<Fun, benchmark_function>::value, int>::type = 0>
502  benchmark_function(Fun&& fun)
503  : f(new model<typename std::decay<Fun>::type>(std::forward<Fun>(fun))) {}
504 
505  benchmark_function(benchmark_function&& that)
506  : f(std::move(that.f)) {}
507 
508  benchmark_function(benchmark_function const& that)
509  : f(that.f->clone()) {}
510 
511  benchmark_function& operator=(benchmark_function&& that) {
512  f = std::move(that.f);
513  return *this;
514  }
515 
516  benchmark_function& operator=(benchmark_function const& that) {
517  f.reset(that.f->clone());
518  return *this;
519  }
520 
521  void operator()(chronometer meter) const { f->call(meter); }
522  private:
523  std::unique_ptr<concept> f;
524  };
525  } // namespace detail
526 } // namespace nonius

546 
547 namespace nonius {
548  namespace detail {
549  template <typename Fun>
550  struct repeater {
551  void operator()(int k) const {
552  for(int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
553  fun();
554  }
555  }
556  Fun fun;
557  };
558  template <typename Fun>
559  repeater<typename std::decay<Fun>::type> repeat(Fun&& fun) {
560  return { std::forward<Fun>(fun) };
561  }
562  } // namespace detail

623 namespace nonius {
624  struct timeout_error : virtual std::exception {
625  public:
626  timeout_error(int seed, int iters) {
627  std::ostringstream ss;
628  ss << "took too long to run; seed: " << seed << ", iters: " << iters;
629  message = ss.str();
630  }
631 
632  char const* what() const NONIUS_NOEXCEPT override {
633  return message.c_str();
634  }
635 
636  private:
637  std::string message;
638  };
639 } // namespace nonius

641 #include <utility>
642 
643 namespace nonius {
644  namespace detail {
645  template <typename Clock = default_clock, typename Fun>
646  TimingOf<Clock, Fun(int)> run_for_at_least(Duration<Clock> how_long, int seed, Fun&& fun) {
647  auto iters = seed;
648  auto start = Clock::now();
649  while(true) {
650  auto now = Clock::now();
651  if(now - start > how_long * 10) {
652  throw timeout_error(seed, iters);
653  }
654  auto r = detail::measure<Clock>(fun, iters);
655  if(r.elapsed >= how_long) {
656  return { r.elapsed, std::move(r.result), iters };
657  }
658  iters *= 2;
659  }
660  }
661  } // namespace detail
662 } // namespace nonius

682 #ifdef __COUNTER__
683 #define NONIUS_DETAIL_UNIQUE_NAME(name) NONIUS_DETAIL_UNIQUE_NAME_LINE(name, __COUNTER__)
684 #else // __COUNTER__
685 #define NONIUS_DETAIL_UNIQUE_NAME(name) NONIUS_DETAIL_UNIQUE_NAME_LINE(name, __LINE__)
686 #endif // __COUNTER__

688 #include <algorithm>
689 #include <functional>
690 #include <string>
691 #include <vector>
692 #include <cmath>
693 
694 namespace nonius {
695  namespace detail {
696  const auto warmup_iterations = 10000;
697  const auto warmup_time = chrono::milliseconds(100);
698  const auto minimum_ticks = 1000;
699  } // namespace detail
700 
701  struct benchmark {
702  benchmark(std::string name, detail::benchmark_function fun)
703  : name(std::move(name)), fun(std::move(fun)) {}
704 
705  void operator()(chronometer meter) const {
706  fun(meter);
707  }
708 
709  template <typename Clock>
710  execution_plan<FloatDuration<Clock>> prepare(configuration cfg, environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> env) const {
711  auto min_time = env.clock_resolution.mean * detail::minimum_ticks;
712  auto run_time = std::min(min_time, decltype(min_time)(detail::warmup_time));
713  auto&& test = detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(chrono::duration_cast<Duration<Clock>>(run_time), 1, [this](int k) {
714  detail::chronometer_model<Clock> model;
715  (*this)(chronometer(model, k));
716  });
717  int new_iters = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(min_time * test.iterations / test.elapsed));
718  return { new_iters, test.elapsed / test.iterations * new_iters * cfg.samples };
719  }
720 
721  template <typename Clock>
722  std::vector<FloatDuration<Clock>> run(configuration cfg, environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> env, execution_plan<FloatDuration<Clock>> plan) const {
723  // warmup a bit
724  detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(chrono::duration_cast<Duration<Clock>>(detail::warmup_time), detail::warmup_iterations, detail::repeat(now<Clock>{}));
725 
726  std::vector<FloatDuration<Clock>> times;
727  times.reserve(cfg.samples);
728  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), cfg.samples, [this, env, plan]{
729  detail::chronometer_model<Clock> model;
730  (*this)(chronometer(model, plan.iterations_per_sample));
731  auto elapsed = model.finished - model.started;
732  auto sample_time = elapsed - env.clock_cost.mean;
733  if(sample_time < FloatDuration<Clock>::zero()) sample_time = FloatDuration<Clock>::zero();
734  return (sample_time / plan.iterations_per_sample);
735  });
736  return times;
737  }
738 
739  std::string name;
740  detail::benchmark_function fun;
741  };
742 
743  using benchmark_registry = std::vector<benchmark>;
744 
745  inline benchmark_registry& global_benchmark_registry() {
746  static benchmark_registry registry;
747  return registry;
748  }
749 
750  struct benchmark_registrar {
751  template <typename Fun>
752  benchmark_registrar(benchmark_registry& registry, std::string name, Fun&& registrant) {
753  registry.emplace_back(std::move(name), std::forward<Fun>(registrant));
754  }
755  };
756 } // namespace nonius

773 // Constructor and destructor helpers
774 
775 #define NONIUS_CONSTRUCTOR_HPP
776 
777 #include <type_traits>
778 
779 namespace nonius {
780  namespace detail {
781  template <typename T, bool Destruct>
782  struct object_storage
783  {
784  typedef typename std::aligned_storage<sizeof(T), std::alignment_of<T>::value>::type TStorage;
785 
786  object_storage() : data() {}
787 
788  object_storage(const object_storage& other)
789  {
790  new(&data) T(other.stored_object());
791  }
792 
793  object_storage(object_storage&& other)
794  {
795  new(&data) T(std::move(other.stored_object()));
796  }
797 
798  ~object_storage() { destruct_on_exit<T>(); }
799 
800  template <typename... Args>
801  void construct(Args&&... args)
802  {
803  new (&data) T(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
804  }
805 
806  template <bool AllowManualDestruction = !Destruct>
807  typename std::enable_if<AllowManualDestruction>::type destruct()
808  {
809  stored_object().~T();
810  }
811 
812  private:
813  // If this is a constructor benchmark, destruct the underlying object
814  template <typename U>
815  void destruct_on_exit(typename std::enable_if<Destruct, U>::type* = 0) { destruct<true>(); }
816  // Otherwise, don't
817  template <typename U>
818  void destruct_on_exit(typename std::enable_if<!Destruct, U>::type* = 0) { }
819 
820  T& stored_object()
821  {
822  return *static_cast<T*>(static_cast<void*>(&data));
823  }
824 
825  TStorage data;
826  };
827  }
828 
829  template <typename T>
830  using storage_for = detail::object_storage<T, true>;
831 
832  template <typename T>
833  using destructable_object = detail::object_storage<T, false>;
834 }

900 namespace nonius {
901  template <typename Duration>
902  struct estimate {
903  Duration point;
904  Duration lower_bound;
905  Duration upper_bound;
906  double confidence_interval;
907 
908  template <typename Duration2>
909  operator estimate<Duration2>() const {
910  return { point, lower_bound, upper_bound, confidence_interval };
911  }
912  };
913 } // namespace nonius

920 namespace nonius {
921  template <typename Duration>
922  struct sample_analysis {
923  std::vector<Duration> samples;
924  estimate<Duration> mean;
925  estimate<Duration> standard_deviation;
926  outlier_classification outliers;
927  double outlier_variance;
928 
929  template <typename Duration2>
930  operator sample_analysis<Duration2>() const {
931  std::vector<Duration2> samples2;
932  samples2.reserve(samples.size());
933  std::transform(samples.begin(), samples.end(), std::back_inserter(samples2), [](Duration d) { return Duration2(d); });
934  return {
935  std::move(samples2),
936  mean,
937  standard_deviation,
938  outliers,
939  outlier_variance,
940  };
941  }
942  };
943 } // namespace nonius

962  struct reporter {

969  } else {
970  auto ofs = std::make_shared<std::ofstream>(cfg.output_file);
971  os = [ofs]() -> std::ostream& { return *ofs; };
972  }
973  report_stream().exceptions(std::ios::failbit);
974  if(!report_stream()) throw bad_stream();
975  do_configure(cfg);

1117 // Pretty printing routines
1118 
1119 #define NONIUS_PRETTY_PRINT_HPP
1120 
1121 #include <ratio>
1122 #include <ios>
1123 #include <iostream>
1124 #include <iomanip>
1125 #include <sstream>
1126 #include <string>
1127 #include <memory>
1128 #include <utility>
1129 
1130 namespace nonius {
1131  namespace detail {
1132  inline double get_magnitude(fp_seconds secs) {
1133  if(secs.count() >= 2.e0) {
1134  return 1.e0;
1135  } else if(secs.count() >= 2.e-3) {
1136  return 1.e3;
1137  } else if(secs.count() >= 2.e-6) {
1138  return 1.e6;
1139  } else {
1140  return 1.e9;
1141  }
1142  }
1143  inline std::string units_for_magnitude(double magnitude) {
1144  if(magnitude <= 1.e0) return "s";
1145  else if(magnitude <= 1.e3) return "ms";
1146  else if(magnitude <= 1.e6) return "ÎĽs";
1147  else return "ns";
1148  }
1149  inline std::string pretty_duration(fp_seconds secs) {
1150  auto magnitude = get_magnitude(secs);
1151  auto units = units_for_magnitude(magnitude);
1152 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1153  if(units == "ÎĽs") units = "us";
1154 #endif
1155  std::ostringstream ss;
1156  ss << std::setprecision(ss.precision());
1157  ss << (secs.count() * magnitude) << ' ' << units;
1158  return ss.str();
1159  }
1160  inline std::string percentage(double d) {
1161  std::ostringstream ss;
1162  ss << std::setprecision(3);
1163  if(d != 0 && d < 1e-5) {
1164  ss << std::fixed;
1165  ss << 0.0001 << "%";
1166  } else {
1167  ss.unsetf(std::ios::floatfield);
1168  ss << (100. * d) << "%";
1169  }
1170  return ss.str();
1171  }
1172  inline std::string percentage_ratio(double part, double whole) {
1173  return percentage(part / whole);
1174  }
1175  } // namespace detail
1176 } // namespace nonius

1178 #include <ratio>
1179 #include <ios>
1180 #include <iostream>
1181 #include <iomanip>
1182 #include <sstream>
1183 #include <string>
1184 #include <memory>

1186 namespace nonius {
1187  struct standard_reporter : reporter {
1188  private:
1189  std::string description() override {
1190  return "the standard reporter";
1191  }
1192 
1193  void do_configure(configuration& cfg) override {
1194  n_samples = cfg.samples;
1195  verbose = cfg.verbose;
1196  summary = cfg.summary;
1197  n_resamples = cfg.resamples;
1198  }
1199 
1200  void do_warmup_start() override {
1201  if(verbose) report_stream() << "warming up\n";
1202  }
1203  void do_estimate_clock_resolution_start() override {
1204  if(verbose) report_stream() << "estimating clock resolution\n";
1205  }
1206  void do_estimate_clock_resolution_complete(environment_estimate<fp_seconds> estimate) override {
1207  if(!summary) {
1208  if(!verbose) report_stream() << "clock resolution: ";
1209  print_environment_estimate(estimate, estimate.outliers.samples_seen + 2);
1210  }
1211  }
1212 
1213  void do_estimate_clock_cost_start() override {
1214  if(verbose) report_stream() << "estimating cost of a clock call\n";
1215  }
1216  void do_estimate_clock_cost_complete(environment_estimate<fp_seconds> estimate) override {
1217  if(verbose) print_environment_estimate(estimate, estimate.outliers.samples_seen);
1218  }
1219 
1220  void do_benchmark_start(std::string const& name) override {
1221  report_stream() << '\n';
1222  if(!summary) report_stream() << "benchmarking ";
1223  report_stream() << name << "\n";
1224  current = name;
1225  }
1226 
1227  void do_measurement_start(execution_plan<fp_seconds> plan) override {
1228  report_stream() << std::setprecision(7);
1229  report_stream().unsetf(std::ios::floatfield);
1230  if(!summary) report_stream() << "collecting " << n_samples << " samples, " << plan.iterations_per_sample << " iterations each, in estimated " << detail::pretty_duration(plan.estimated_duration) << "\n";
1231  }
1232  void do_analysis_start() override {
1233  if(verbose) report_stream() << "bootstrapping with " << n_resamples << " resamples\n";
1234  }
1235  void do_benchmark_failure(std::exception_ptr) override {
1236  error_stream() << current << " failed to run successfully\n";
1237  report_stream() << "benchmark aborted\n";
1238  }
1239  void do_analysis_complete(sample_analysis<fp_seconds> const& analysis) override {
1240  print_statistic_estimate("mean", analysis.mean);
1241  print_statistic_estimate("std dev", analysis.standard_deviation);
1242  if(!summary) print_outliers(analysis.outliers);
1243  if(verbose) report_stream() << "variance introduced by outliers: " << detail::percentage(analysis.outlier_variance) << "\n";
1244  const char* effect;
1245  if(analysis.outlier_variance < 0.01) {
1246  effect = "unaffected";
1247  } else if(analysis.outlier_variance < 0.1) {
1248  effect = "slightly inflated";
1249  } else if(analysis.outlier_variance < 0.5) {
1250  effect = "moderately inflated";
1251  } else {
1252  effect = "severely inflated";
1253  }
1254  report_stream() << "variance is " << effect << " by outliers\n";
1255  }
1256 
1257  void print_environment_estimate(environment_estimate<fp_seconds> e, int iterations) {
1258  report_stream() << std::setprecision(7);
1259  report_stream().unsetf(std::ios::floatfield);
1260  report_stream() << "mean is " << detail::pretty_duration(e.mean) << " (" << iterations << " iterations)\n";
1261  if(verbose) print_outliers(e.outliers);
1262  }
1263  void print_outlier_count(const char* description, int count, int total) {
1264  if(count > 0) report_stream() << " " << count << " (" << detail::percentage_ratio(count, total) << ") " << description << "\n";
1265  }
1266  void print_outliers(outlier_classification o) {
1267  report_stream() << "found " << o.total() << " outliers among " << o.samples_seen << " samples (" << detail::percentage_ratio(o.total(), o.samples_seen) << ")\n";
1268  if(verbose) {
1269  print_outlier_count("low severe", o.low_severe, o.samples_seen);
1270  print_outlier_count("low mild", o.low_mild, o.samples_seen);
1271  print_outlier_count("high mild", o.high_mild, o.samples_seen);
1272  print_outlier_count("high severe", o.high_severe, o.samples_seen);
1273  }
1274  }
1275  void print_statistic_estimate(const char* name, estimate<fp_seconds> estimate) {
1276  report_stream() << std::setprecision(7);
1277  report_stream().unsetf(std::ios::floatfield);
1278  report_stream() << name << ": " << detail::pretty_duration(estimate.point);
1279  if(!summary) {
1280  report_stream() << ", lb " << detail::pretty_duration(estimate.lower_bound)
1281  << ", ub " << detail::pretty_duration(estimate.upper_bound)
1282  << ", ci " << std::setprecision(3) << estimate.confidence_interval;
1283  }
1284  report_stream() << "\n";
1285  }
1286 
1287  int n_samples = 0;
1288  int n_resamples = 0;
1289  bool verbose = false;
1290  bool summary = false;
1291 
1292  std::string current;
1293  };
1294 
1295  NONIUS_REPORTER("", standard_reporter);
1296  NONIUS_REPORTER("standard", standard_reporter);
1297 } // namespace nonius

1348  using sample = std::vector<double>;
1349 
1350  template <typename Iterator>
1351  double weighted_average_quantile(int k, int q, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
1352  auto count = last - first;
1353  double idx = (count - 1) * k /static_cast<double>(q);
1354  int j = static_cast<int>(idx);
1355  double g = idx - j;
1356  std::nth_element(first, first+j, last);
1357  auto xj = first[j];
1358  if(g == 0) return xj;
1359 
1360  auto xj1 = *std::min_element(first+(j+1), last);
1361  return xj + g * (xj1 - xj);
1362  }
1363 
1364  template <typename Iterator>
1365  outlier_classification classify_outliers(Iterator first, Iterator last) {
1366  std::vector<double> copy(first, last);
1367 
1368  auto q1 = weighted_average_quantile(1, 4, copy.begin(), copy.end());
1369  auto q3 = weighted_average_quantile(3, 4, copy.begin(), copy.end());
1370  auto iqr = q3 - q1;
1371  auto los = q1 - (iqr * 3.);
1372  auto lom = q1 - (iqr * 1.5);
1373  auto him = q3 + (iqr * 1.5);
1374  auto his = q3 + (iqr * 3.);
1375 
1376  outlier_classification o;
1377  for(; first != last; ++first) {
1378  auto&& t = *first;
1379  if(t < los) ++o.low_severe;
1380  else if(t < lom) ++o.low_mild;
1381  else if(t > his) ++o.high_severe;
1382  else if(t > him) ++o.high_mild;
1383  ++o.samples_seen;
1384  }
1385  return o;
1386  }
1387 
1388  template <typename Iterator>
1389  double mean(Iterator first, Iterator last) {
1390  auto count = last - first;
1391  double sum = std::accumulate(first, last, 0.);
1392  return sum / count;
1393  }
1394 
1395  template <typename Iterator>
1396  double standard_deviation(Iterator first, Iterator last) {
1397  auto m = mean(first, last);
1398  double variance = std::accumulate(first, last, 0., [m](double a, double b) {
1399  double diff = b - m;
1400  return a + diff*diff;
1401  }) / (last - first);
1402  return std::sqrt(variance);
1403  }
1404 
1405  template <typename URng, typename Iterator, typename Estimator>
1406  sample resample(URng& rng, int resamples, Iterator first, Iterator last, Estimator& estimator) {
1407  auto n = last - first;
1408  std::uniform_int_distribution<decltype(n)> dist(0, n-1);
1409 
1410  sample out;
1411  out.reserve(resamples);
1412  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(out), resamples, [n, first, &estimator, &dist, &rng] {
1413  std::vector<double> resampled;
1414  resampled.reserve(n);
1415  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(resampled), n, [first, &dist, &rng] { return first[dist(rng)]; });
1416  return estimator(resampled.begin(), resampled.end());
1417  });
1418  std::sort(out.begin(), out.end());
1419  return out;
1420  }
1421 
1422  template <typename Estimator, typename Iterator>
1423  sample jackknife(Estimator&& estimator, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
1424  auto n = last - first;
1425  auto second = std::next(first);
1426  sample results;
1427  results.reserve(n);
1428 
1429  for(auto it = first; it != last; ++it) {
1430  std::iter_swap(it, first);
1431  results.push_back(estimator(second, last));
1432  }
1433 
1434  return results;
1435  }
1436 
1437  template <typename Iterator, typename Estimator>
1438  estimate<double> bootstrap(double confidence_level, Iterator first, Iterator last, sample const& resample, Estimator&& estimator) {
1439  namespace bm = boost::math;
1440 
1441  auto n_samples = last - first;
1442 
1443  double point = estimator(first, last);
1444  // Degenerate case with a single sample
1445  if(n_samples == 1) return { point, point, point, confidence_level };
1446 
1447  sample jack = jackknife(estimator, first, last);
1448  double jack_mean = mean(jack.begin(), jack.end());
1449  double sum_squares, sum_cubes;
1450  std::tie(sum_squares, sum_cubes) = std::accumulate(jack.begin(), jack.end(), std::make_pair(0., 0.), [jack_mean](std::pair<double, double> sqcb, double x) -> std::pair<double, double> {
1451  auto d = jack_mean - x;
1452  auto d2 = d * d;
1453  auto d3 = d2 * d;
1454  return { sqcb.first + d2, sqcb.second + d3 };
1455  });
1456 
1457  double accel = sum_cubes / (6 * std::pow(sum_squares, 1.5));
1458  int n = static_cast<int>(resample.size());
1459  double prob_n = std::count_if(resample.begin(), resample.end(), [point](double x) { return x < point; }) /(double) n;
1460  // degenerate case with uniform samples
1461  if(prob_n == 0) return { point, point, point, confidence_level };
1462 
1463  double bias = bm::quantile(bm::normal{}, prob_n);
1464  double z1 = bm::quantile(bm::normal{}, (1. - confidence_level) / 2.);
1465 
1466  auto cumn = [n](double x) -> int { return std::lround(bm::cdf(bm::normal{}, x) * n); };
1467  auto a = [bias, accel](double b) { return bias + b / (1. - accel * b); };
1468  double b1 = bias + z1;
1469  double b2 = bias - z1;
1470  double a1 = a(b1);
1471  double a2 = a(b2);
1472  auto lo = std::max(cumn(a1), 0);
1473  auto hi = std::min(cumn(a2), n - 1);
1474 
1475  return { point, resample[lo], resample[hi], confidence_level };
1476  }
1477 
1478  inline double outlier_variance(estimate<double> mean, estimate<double> stddev, int n) {
1479  double sb = stddev.point;
1480  double mn = mean.point / n;
1481  double mg_min = mn / 2.;
1482  double sg = std::min(mg_min / 4., sb / std::sqrt(n));
1483  double sg2 = sg * sg;
1484  double sb2 = sb * sb;
1485 
1486  auto c_max = [n, mn, sb2, sg2](double x) -> double {
1487  double k = mn - x;
1488  double d = k * k;
1489  double nd = n * d;
1490  double k0 = -n * nd;
1491  double k1 = sb2 - n * sg2 + nd;
1492  double det = k1 * k1 - 4 * sg2 * k0;
1493  return (int)(-2. * k0 / (k1 + std::sqrt(det)));
1494  };
1495 
1496  auto var_out = [n, sb2, sg2](double c) {
1497  double nc = n - c;
1498  return (nc / n) * (sb2 - nc * sg2);
1499  };
1500 
1501  return std::min(var_out(1), var_out(std::min(c_max(0.), c_max(mg_min)))) / sb2;
1502  }
1503 
1504  struct bootstrap_analysis {
1505  estimate<double> mean;
1506  estimate<double> standard_deviation;
1507  double outlier_variance;
1508  };
1509 
1510  template <typename Iterator>
1511  bootstrap_analysis analyse_samples(double confidence_level, int n_resamples, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
1512  static std::random_device entropy;
1513 
1514  auto n = static_cast<int>(last - first); // seriously, one can't use integral types without hell in C++
1515 
1516  auto mean = &detail::mean<Iterator>;
1517  auto stddev = &detail::standard_deviation<Iterator>;
1518 
1519  auto estimate = [=](double(*f)(Iterator, Iterator)) {
1520  auto seed = entropy();
1521  return std::async(std::launch::async, [=]{
1522  std::mt19937 rng(seed);
1523  auto resampled = resample(rng, n_resamples, first, last, f);
1524  return bootstrap(confidence_level, first, last, resampled, f);
1525  });
1526  };
1527 
1528  auto mean_future = estimate(mean);
1529  auto stddev_future = estimate(stddev);
1530 
1531  auto mean_estimate = mean_future.get();
1532  auto stddev_estimate = stddev_future.get();
1533 
1534  double outlier_variance = detail::outlier_variance(mean_estimate, stddev_estimate, n);
1535 
1536  return { mean_estimate, stddev_estimate, outlier_variance };
1537  }
1538  } // namespace detail
1539 } // namespace nonius

1547 namespace nonius {
1548  namespace detail {
1549  template <typename Clock>
1550  std::vector<double> resolution(int k) {
1551  std::vector<TimePoint<Clock>> times;
1552  times.reserve(k+1);
1553  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), k+1, now<Clock>{});
1554 
1555  std::vector<double> deltas;
1556  deltas.reserve(k);
1557  std::transform(std::next(times.begin()), times.end(), times.begin(),
1558  std::back_inserter(deltas),
1559  [](TimePoint<Clock> a, TimePoint<Clock> b) { return static_cast<double>((a - b).count()); });
1560 
1561  return deltas;
1562  }
1563 
1564  const auto warmup_seed = 10000;
1565  const auto clock_resolution_estimation_time = chrono::milliseconds(500);
1566  const auto clock_cost_estimation_time_limit = chrono::seconds(1);
1567  const auto clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit = 100000;
1568  const auto clock_cost_estimation_time = chrono::milliseconds(10);
1569  const auto clock_cost_estimation_iterations = 10000;
1570 
1571  template <typename Clock>
1572  int warmup() {
1573  return run_for_at_least<Clock>(chrono::duration_cast<Duration<Clock>>(warmup_time), warmup_seed, &resolution<Clock>)
1574  .iterations;
1575  }
1576  template <typename Clock>
1577  environment_estimate<FloatDuration<Clock>> estimate_clock_resolution(int iterations) {
1578  auto r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(chrono::duration_cast<Duration<Clock>>(clock_resolution_estimation_time), iterations, &resolution<Clock>)
1579  .result;
1580  return {
1581  FloatDuration<Clock>(mean(r.begin(), r.end())),
1582  classify_outliers(r.begin(), r.end()),
1583  };
1584  }
1585  template <typename Clock>
1586  environment_estimate<FloatDuration<Clock>> estimate_clock_cost(FloatDuration<Clock> resolution) {
1587  auto time_limit = std::min(resolution * clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit, FloatDuration<Clock>(clock_cost_estimation_time_limit));
1588  auto time_clock = [](int k) {
1589  return detail::measure<Clock>([k]{
1590  for(int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
1591  volatile auto ignored = Clock::now();
1592  (void)ignored;
1593  }
1594  }).elapsed;
1595  };
1596  time_clock(1);
1597  int iters = clock_cost_estimation_iterations;
1598  auto&& r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(chrono::duration_cast<Duration<Clock>>(clock_cost_estimation_time), iters, time_clock);
1599  std::vector<double> times;
1600  int nsamples = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(time_limit / r.elapsed));
1601  times.reserve(nsamples);
1602  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), nsamples, [time_clock, &r]{
1603  return (time_clock(r.iterations) / r.iterations).count();
1604  });
1605  return {
1606  FloatDuration<Clock>(mean(times.begin(), times.end())),
1607  classify_outliers(times.begin(), times.end()),
1608  };
1609  }
1610  } // namespace detail
1611 } // namespace nonius

1625 // Run and analyse one benchmark

1627 #define NONIUS_DETAIL_ANALYSE_HPP

1629 #include <algorithm>
1630 #include <iterator>
1631 #include <vector>
1632 
1633 namespace nonius {
1634  namespace detail {
1635  template <typename Duration, typename Iterator>
1636  sample_analysis<Duration> analyse(configuration cfg, environment<Duration>, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
1637  std::vector<double> samples;
1638  samples.reserve(last - first);
1639  std::transform(first, last, std::back_inserter(samples), [](Duration d) { return d.count(); });
1640 
1641  auto analysis = nonius::detail::analyse_samples(cfg.confidence_interval, cfg.resamples, samples.begin(), samples.end());
1642  auto outliers = nonius::detail::classify_outliers(samples.begin(), samples.end());
1643 
1644  auto wrap_estimate = [](estimate<double> e) {
1645  return estimate<Duration> {
1646  Duration(e.point),
1647  Duration(e.lower_bound),
1648  Duration(e.upper_bound),
1649  e.confidence_interval,
1650  };
1651  };
1652  std::vector<Duration> samples2;
1653  samples2.reserve(samples.size());
1654  std::transform(samples.begin(), samples.end(), std::back_inserter(samples2), [](double d) { return Duration(d); });
1655  return {
1656  std::move(samples2),
1657  wrap_estimate(analysis.mean),
1658  wrap_estimate(analysis.standard_deviation),
1659  outliers,
1660  analysis.outlier_variance,
1661  };
1662  }
1663  } // namespace detail
1664 } // namespace nonius

1671 namespace nonius {
1672  namespace detail {
1673  template <typename Clock>
1674  environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> measure_environment(reporter& rep) {
1675  rep.warmup_start();
1676  auto iters = detail::warmup<Clock>();
1677  rep.warmup_end(iters);
1678 
1679  rep.estimate_clock_resolution_start();
1680  auto resolution = detail::estimate_clock_resolution<Clock>(iters);
1681  rep.estimate_clock_resolution_complete(resolution);
1682 
1683  rep.estimate_clock_cost_start();
1684  auto cost = detail::estimate_clock_cost<Clock>(resolution.mean);
1685  rep.estimate_clock_cost_complete(cost);
1686 
1687  return { resolution, cost };
1688  }
1689  } // namespace detail
1690 
1691  struct benchmark_user_error : virtual std::exception {
1692  char const* what() const NONIUS_NOEXCEPT override {
1693  return "a benchmark failed to run successfully";
1694  }
1695  };
1696 
1697  template <typename Fun>
1698  detail::CompleteType<detail::ResultOf<Fun()>> user_code(reporter& rep, Fun&& fun) {
1699  try {
1700  return detail::complete_invoke(std::forward<Fun>(fun));
1701  } catch(...) {
1702  rep.benchmark_failure(std::current_exception());
1703  throw benchmark_user_error();
1704  }
1705  }
1706 
1707  template <typename Clock = default_clock, typename Iterator>
1708  void go(configuration cfg, Iterator first, Iterator last, reporter& rep) {
1709  rep.configure(cfg);
1710 
1711  auto env = detail::measure_environment<Clock>(rep);
1712 
1713  rep.suite_start();
1714 
1715  for(; first != last; ++first) {
1716  try {
1717  rep.benchmark_start(first->name);
1718 
1719  auto plan = user_code(rep, [&first, &cfg, &env]{ return first->template prepare<Clock>(cfg, env); });
1720  rep.measurement_start(plan);
1721  auto samples = user_code(rep, [&first, &cfg, &env, &plan]{ return first->template run<Clock>(cfg, env, plan); });
1722  rep.measurement_complete(std::vector<fp_seconds>(samples.begin(), samples.end()));
1723 
1724  if(!cfg.no_analysis) {
1725  rep.analysis_start();
1726  auto analysis = detail::analyse(cfg, env, samples.begin(), samples.end());
1727  rep.analysis_complete(analysis);
1728  }
1729 
1730  rep.benchmark_complete();
1731  } catch(benchmark_user_error const&) {
1732  continue;
1733  }
1734  }
1735 
1736  rep.suite_complete();
1737  }
1738  struct duplicate_benchmarks : virtual std::exception {
1739  char const* what() const NONIUS_NOEXCEPT override {
1740  return "two or more benchmarks with the same name were registered";
1741  }
1742  };
1743  template <typename Clock = default_clock, typename Iterator>
1744  void validate_benchmarks(Iterator first, Iterator last) {
1745  struct strings_lt_through_pointer {
1746  bool operator()(std::string* a, std::string* b) const { return *a < *b; };
1747  };
1748  std::set<std::string*, strings_lt_through_pointer> names;
1749  for(; first != last; ++first) {
1750  if(!names.insert(&first->name).second)
1751  throw duplicate_benchmarks();
1752  }
1753  }
1754  template <typename Clock = default_clock, typename Iterator>
1755  void go(configuration cfg, Iterator first, Iterator last, reporter&& rep) {
1756  go(cfg, first, last, rep);
1757  }
1758  struct no_such_reporter : virtual std::exception {
1759  char const* what() const NONIUS_NOEXCEPT override {
1760  return "reporter could not be found";
1761  }
1762  };
1763  template <typename Clock = default_clock>
1764  void go(configuration cfg, benchmark_registry& benchmarks = global_benchmark_registry(), reporter_registry& reporters = global_reporter_registry()) {
1765  auto it = reporters.find(cfg.reporter);
1766  if(it == reporters.end()) throw no_such_reporter();
1767  validate_benchmarks(benchmarks.begin(), benchmarks.end());
1768  go(cfg, benchmarks.begin(), benchmarks.end(), *it->second);
1769  }

1788 #define NONIUS_REPORTERS_CSV_REPORTER_HPP
1789 
1790 #include <ios>

1795 #include <limits>

1799 namespace nonius {
1800  struct csv_reporter : reporter {
1801  private:
1802  std::string description() override {
1803  return "outputs samples to a CSV file";
1804  }
1805 
1806  void do_configure(configuration& cfg) override {
1807  cfg.no_analysis = true;
1808  n_samples = cfg.samples;
1809  verbose = cfg.verbose;
1810  }
1811 
1812  void do_warmup_start() override {
1813  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "warming up\n";
1814  }
1815  void do_estimate_clock_resolution_start() override {
1816  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "estimating clock resolution\n";
1817  }
1818  void do_estimate_clock_cost_start() override {
1819  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "estimating cost of a clock call\n";
1820  }
1821 
1822  void do_benchmark_start(std::string const& name) override {
1823  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "\nbenchmarking " << name << "\n";
1824  current = name;
1825  }
1826 
1827  void do_measurement_start(execution_plan<fp_seconds> plan) override {
1828  report_stream() << std::setprecision(7);
1829  report_stream().unsetf(std::ios::floatfield);
1830  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "collecting " << n_samples << " samples, " << plan.iterations_per_sample << " iterations each, in estimated " << detail::pretty_duration(plan.estimated_duration) << "\n";
1831  }
1832  void do_measurement_complete(std::vector<fp_seconds> const& samples) override {
1833  data[current] = samples;
1834  }
1835 
1836  void do_benchmark_failure(std::exception_ptr) override {
1837  error_stream() << current << " failed to run successfully\n";
1838  }
1839 
1840  void do_suite_complete() override {
1841  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "\ngenerating CSV report\n";
1842  report_stream() << std::fixed;
1843  report_stream().precision(std::numeric_limits<double>::digits10);
1844  bool first = true;
1845  for(auto&& kv : data) {
1846  if(!first) report_stream() << ",";
1847  report_stream() << "\"" << escape(kv.first) << "\""; // TODO escape
1848  first = false;
1849  }
1850  report_stream() << "\n";
1851  for(int i = 0; i < n_samples; ++i) {
1852  first = true;
1853  for(auto&& kv : data) {
1854  if(!first) report_stream() << ",";
1855  report_stream() << kv.second[i].count();
1856  first = false;
1857  }
1858  report_stream() << "\n";
1859  }
1860  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "done\n";
1861  }
1862 
1863  private:
1864  static std::string escape(std::string const& source) {
1865  auto first = source.begin();
1866  auto last = source.end();
1867 
1868  auto quotes = std::count(first, last, '"');
1869  if(quotes == 0) return source;
1870 
1871  std::string escaped;
1872  escaped.reserve(source.size() + quotes);
1873 
1874  while(first != last) {
1875  auto next_quote = std::find(first, last, '"');
1876  std::copy(first, next_quote, std::back_inserter(escaped));
1877  first = next_quote;
1878  if(first != last) {
1879  ++first;
1880  escaped.push_back('"');
1881  escaped.push_back('"');
1882  }
1883  }
1884 
1885  return escaped;
1886  }
1887 
1888  int n_samples;
1889  bool verbose;
1890  std::string current;
1891  std::unordered_map<std::string, std::vector<fp_seconds>> data;
1892  };

1927 // General escaping routines
1928 
1929 #define NONIUS_DETAIL_ESCAPE_HPP
1930 
1931 #include <string>
1932 #include <algorithm>
1933 #include <iterator>
1934 #include <utility>
1935 
1936 namespace nonius {
1937  namespace detail {
1938  inline std::string escape(std::string const& source, std::unordered_map<char, std::string> const& escapes) {
1939  std::string magic;
1940  magic.reserve(escapes.size());
1941  std::transform(escapes.begin(), escapes.end(), std::back_inserter(magic), [](std::pair<char const, std::string> const& p) { return p.first; });
1942 
1943  auto first = source.begin();
1944  auto last = source.end();
1945 
1946  auto n_magic = std::count_if(first, last, [&magic](char c) { return magic.find(c) != std::string::npos; });
1947 
1948  std::string escaped;
1949  escaped.reserve(source.size() + n_magic*6);
1950 
1951  while(first != last) {
1952  auto next_magic = std::find_first_of(first, last, magic.begin(), magic.end());
1953  std::copy(first, next_magic, std::back_inserter(escaped));
1954  first = next_magic;
1955  if(first != last) {
1956  auto it = escapes.find(*first);
1957  if(it != escapes.end()) {
1958  escaped += it->second;
1959  }
1960  ++first;
1961  }
1962  }
1963  return escaped;
1964  }
1965  } // namespace detail
1966 } // namespace nonius

1969 #include <iomanip>
1970 #include <algorithm>

1978 namespace nonius {
1979  struct junit_reporter : reporter {
1980  private:
1981  std::string description() override {
1982  return "outputs results to a JUnit-compatible XML file";
1983  }
1984 
1985  void do_configure(configuration& cfg) override {
1986  n_samples = cfg.samples;
1987  confidence_interval = cfg.confidence_interval;
1988  resamples = cfg.resamples;
1989  verbose = cfg.verbose;
1990  title = cfg.title;
1991  }
1992 
1993  struct result {
1994  sample_analysis<fp_seconds> analysis;
1995  std::exception_ptr failure;
1996  };
1997 
1998  void do_warmup_start() override {
1999  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "warming up\n";
2000  }
2001  void do_estimate_clock_resolution_start() override {
2002  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "estimating clock resolution\n";
2003  }
2004  void do_estimate_clock_cost_start() override {
2005  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "estimating cost of a clock call\n";
2006  }
2007 
2008  void do_benchmark_start(std::string const& name) override {
2009  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "\nbenchmarking " << name << "\n";
2010  current = name;
2011  }
2012 
2013  void do_measurement_start(execution_plan<fp_seconds> plan) override {
2014  report_stream() << std::setprecision(7);
2015  report_stream().unsetf(std::ios::floatfield);
2016  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "collecting " << n_samples << " samples, " << plan.iterations_per_sample << " iterations each, in estimated " << detail::pretty_duration(plan.estimated_duration) << "\n";
2017  }
2018 
2019  void do_analysis_start() override {
2020  if(verbose) report_stream() << "analysing samples\n";
2021  }
2022  void do_analysis_complete(sample_analysis<fp_seconds> const& analysis) override {
2023  data[current] = { analysis, nullptr };
2024  }
2025 
2026  void do_benchmark_failure(std::exception_ptr e) override {
2027  data[current] = { sample_analysis<fp_seconds>(), e };
2028  error_stream() << current << " failed to run successfully\n";
2029  }
2030 
2031  void do_suite_complete() override {
2032  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "\ngenerating JUnit report\n";
2033 
2034  report_stream() << "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n";
2035  report_stream() << "<testsuite name=\"" << escape(title) << "\" tests=\"" << data.size() << "\"";
2036  auto failures = std::count_if(data.begin(), data.end(),
2037  [](std::pair<std::string const&, result> const& p) {
2038  return static_cast<bool>(p.second.failure);
2039  });
2040  if(failures > 0) report_stream() << " errors=\"" << failures << "\"";
2041  report_stream() << ">\n";
2042 
2043  report_stream() << " <properties>\n";
2044  report_stream() << " <property name=\"samples\" value=\"" << n_samples << "\">\n";
2045  report_stream() << " <property name=\"confidence_interval\" value=\"" << std::setprecision(3) << confidence_interval << "\">\n";
2046  report_stream() << " <property name=\"resamples\" value=\"" << resamples << "\">\n";
2047  report_stream() << " </properties>\n";
2048 
2049  for(auto tc : data) {
2050  report_stream() << " <testcase name=\"" << escape(tc.first) << "\"";
2051  if(tc.second.failure) {
2052  report_stream() << ">\n";
2053  try {
2054  std::rethrow_exception(tc.second.failure);
2055  } catch(std::exception const& e) {
2056  report_stream() << " <error message=\"" << escape(e.what()) << "\" />\n";
2057  } catch(...) {
2058  report_stream() << " <error message=\"unknown error\" />\n";
2059  }
2060  report_stream() << " </testcase>\n";
2061  } else {
2062  report_stream() << std::fixed;
2063  report_stream().precision(std::numeric_limits<double>::digits10);
2064  report_stream() << " time=\"" << tc.second.analysis.mean.point.count() << "\" />\n";
2065  }
2066  }
2067 
2068  report_stream() << "</testsuite>\n";
2069 
2070  report_stream() << std::flush;
2071 
2072  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "done\n";
2073  }
2074 
2075  static std::string escape(std::string const& source) {
2076  static const std::unordered_map<char, std::string> escapes {
2077  { '\'', "&apos;" },
2078  { '"', "&quot;" },
2079  { '<', "&lt;" },
2080  { '>', "&gt;" },
2081  { '&', "&amp;" },
2082  };
2083  return detail::escape(source, escapes);
2084  }
2085 
2086  int n_samples;
2087  double confidence_interval;
2088  int resamples;
2089  bool verbose;
2090  std::string title;
2091 
2092  std::string current;
2093  std::unordered_map<std::string, result> data;
2094  };
2095

2495  // parse_val
2497  inline data_ptr parse_val(std::string key, data_map &data)
2498  {
2499  // quoted string
2500  if (key[0] == '\"')
2501  {
2502  return make_data(boost::trim_copy_if(key, [](char c){ return c == '"'; }));
2503  }
2504  // check for dotted notation, i.e [foo.bar]
2505  size_t index = key.find(".") ;
2506  if (index == std::string::npos)
2507  {
2508  if (!data.has(key))
2509  {
2510  return make_data("{$" + key + "}") ;
2511  }
2512  return data[key] ;
2513  }
2514 
2515  std::string sub_key = key.substr(0, index) ;
2516  if (!data.has(sub_key))
2517  {
2518  return make_data("{$" + key + "}") ;
2519  }
2520  data_ptr item = data[sub_key] ;
2521  return parse_val(key.substr(index+1), item->getmap()) ;
2522  }

2549 
2550  // TokenVar
2551  inline TokenType TokenVar::gettype()
2552  {
2553  return TOKEN_TYPE_VAR ;
2554  }
2555 
2556  inline void TokenVar::gettext( std::ostream &stream, data_map &data )
2557  {
2558  stream << parse_val(m_key, data)->getvalue() ;
2559  }
2560 
2561  // TokenFor
2562  inline TokenFor::TokenFor(std::string expr)
2563  {
2564  std::vector<std::string> elements ;
2565  boost::split(elements, expr, boost::is_space()) ;
2566  if (elements.size() != 4u)
2567  {
2568  throw TemplateException("Invalid syntax in for statement") ;
2569  }
2570  m_val = elements[1] ;
2571  m_key = elements[3] ;
2572  }
2573 
2574  inline TokenType TokenFor::gettype()
2575  {
2576  return TOKEN_TYPE_FOR ;
2577  }
2578 
2579  inline void TokenFor::gettext( std::ostream &stream, data_map &data )
2580  {
2581  data_ptr value = parse_val(m_key, data) ;
2582  data_list &items = value->getlist() ;
2583  for (size_t i = 0 ; i < items.size() ; ++i)
2584  {
2585  data_map loop ;
2586  loop["index"] = make_data(boost::lexical_cast<std::string>(i+1)) ;
2587  loop["index0"] = make_data(boost::lexical_cast<std::string>(i)) ;
2588  data["loop"] = make_data(loop);
2589  data[m_val] = items[i] ;
2590  for(size_t j = 0 ; j < m_children.size() ; ++j)
2591  {
2592  m_children[j]->gettext(stream, data) ;
2593  }
2594  }
2595  }
2596 
2597  inline void TokenFor::set_children( token_vector &children )
2598  {
2599  m_children.assign(children.begin(), children.end()) ;
2600  }
2601 
2602  inline token_vector & TokenFor::get_children()
2603  {
2604  return m_children;
2605  }
2606 
2607  // TokenIf
2608  inline TokenType TokenIf::gettype()
2609  {
2610  return TOKEN_TYPE_IF ;
2611  }
2612 
2613  inline void TokenIf::gettext( std::ostream &stream, data_map &data )
2614  {
2615  if (is_true(m_expr, data))
2616  {
2617  for(size_t j = 0 ; j < m_children.size() ; ++j)
2618  {
2619  m_children[j]->gettext(stream, data) ;
2620  }
2621  }
2622  }
2623 
2624  inline bool TokenIf::is_true( std::string expr, data_map &data )
2625  {
2626  std::vector<std::string> elements ;
2627  boost::split(elements, expr, boost::is_space()) ;
2628 
2629  if (elements[1] == "not")
2630  {
2631  return parse_val(elements[2], data)->empty() ;
2632  }
2633  if (elements.size() == 2)
2634  {
2635  return ! parse_val(elements[1], data)->empty() ;
2636  }
2637  data_ptr lhs = parse_val(elements[1], data) ;
2638  data_ptr rhs = parse_val(elements[3], data) ;
2639  if (elements[2] == "==")
2640  {
2641  return lhs->getvalue() == rhs->getvalue() ;
2642  }
2643  return lhs->getvalue() != rhs->getvalue() ;
2644  }
2645 
2646  inline void TokenIf::set_children( token_vector &children )
2647  {
2648  m_children.assign(children.begin(), children.end()) ;
2649  }
2650 
2651  inline token_vector & TokenIf::get_children()
2652  {
2653  return m_children;
2654  }
2655 
2656  // TokenEnd
2657  inline TokenType TokenEnd::gettype()
2658  {
2659  return m_type == "endfor" ? TOKEN_TYPE_ENDFOR : TOKEN_TYPE_ENDIF ;
2660  }
2661 
2662  inline void TokenEnd::gettext( std::ostream &, data_map &)
2663  {
2664  throw TemplateException("End-of-control statements have no associated text") ;
2665  }
2666 
2667  // gettext
2668  // generic helper for getting text from tokens.
2669 
2670  inline std::string gettext(token_ptr token, data_map &data)
2671  {
2672  std::ostringstream stream ;
2673  token->gettext(stream, data) ;
2674  return stream.str() ;
2675  }
2677  // parse_tree
2678  // recursively parses list of tokens into a tree
2680  inline void parse_tree(token_vector &tokens, token_vector &tree, TokenType until)
2681  {
2682  while(! tokens.empty())
2683  {
2684  // 'pops' first item off list
2685  token_ptr token = tokens[0] ;
2686  tokens.erase(tokens.begin()) ;
2687 
2688  if (token->gettype() == TOKEN_TYPE_FOR)
2689  {
2690  token_vector children ;
2691  parse_tree(tokens, children, TOKEN_TYPE_ENDFOR) ;
2692  token->set_children(children) ;
2693  }
2694  else if (token->gettype() == TOKEN_TYPE_IF)
2695  {
2696  token_vector children ;
2697  parse_tree(tokens, children, TOKEN_TYPE_ENDIF) ;
2698  token->set_children(children) ;
2699  }
2700  else if (token->gettype() == until)
2701  {
2702  return ;
2703  }
2704  tree.push_back(token) ;
2705  }
2706  }
2708  // tokenize
2709  // parses a template into tokens (text, for, if, variable)
2711  inline token_vector & tokenize(std::string text, token_vector &tokens)
2712  {
2713  while(! text.empty())
2714  {
2715  size_t pos = text.find("{") ;
2716  if (pos == std::string::npos)
2717  {
2718  if (! text.empty())
2719  {
2720  tokens.push_back(token_ptr(new TokenText(text))) ;
2721  }
2722  return tokens ;
2723  }
2724  std::string pre_text = text.substr(0, pos) ;
2725  if (! pre_text.empty())
2726  {
2727  tokens.push_back(token_ptr(new TokenText(pre_text))) ;
2728  }
2729  text = text.substr(pos+1) ;
2730  if (text.empty())
2731  {
2732  tokens.push_back(token_ptr(new TokenText("{"))) ;
2733  return tokens ;
2734  }
2735 
2736  // variable
2737  if (text[0] == '$')
2738  {
2739  pos = text.find("}") ;
2740  if (pos != std::string::npos)
2741  {
2742  tokens.push_back(token_ptr (new TokenVar(text.substr(1, pos-1)))) ;
2743  text = text.substr(pos+1) ;
2744  }
2745  }
2746  // control statement
2747  else if (text[0] == '%')
2748  {
2749  pos = text.find("}") ;
2750  if (pos != std::string::npos)
2751  {
2752  std::string expression = boost::trim_copy(text.substr(1, pos-2)) ;
2753  text = text.substr(pos+1) ;
2754  if (boost::starts_with(expression, "for"))
2755  {
2756  tokens.push_back(token_ptr (new TokenFor(expression))) ;
2757  }
2758  else if (boost::starts_with(expression, "if"))
2759  {
2760  tokens.push_back(token_ptr (new TokenIf(expression))) ;
2761  }
2762  else
2763  {
2764  tokens.push_back(token_ptr (new TokenEnd(boost::trim_copy(expression)))) ;
2765  }
2766  }
2767  }
2768  else
2769  {
2770  tokens.push_back(token_ptr(new TokenText("{"))) ;
2771  }
2772  }
2773  return tokens ;
2774  }
2775 
2776  inline std::string parse(std::string templ_text, data_map &data)
2777  {
2778  std::ostringstream stream ;
2779  parse(stream, templ_text, data) ;
2780  return stream.str() ;
2781  }
2782  inline void parse(std::ostream &stream, std::string templ_text, data_map &data)
2783  {
2784  token_vector tokens ;
2785  tokenize(templ_text, tokens) ;
2786  token_vector tree ;
2787  parse_tree(tokens, tree) ;
2788 
2789  for (size_t i = 0 ; i < tree.size() ; ++i)
2790  {
2791  // Recursively calls gettext on each node in the tree.
2792  // gettext returns the appropriate text for that node.
2793  // for text, itself;
2794  // for variable, substitution;
2795  // for control statement, recursively gets kids
2796  tree[i]->gettext(stream, data) ;
2797  }
2798  }
2799 }

3333  void do_suite_complete() override {
3334  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "\ngenerating HTML report\n";
3335 
3336  auto&& templ = template_string();
3337 
3338  auto magnitude = ideal_magnitude();
3339 
3340  cpptempl::data_map map;
3341  map["title"] = escape(title);
3342  map["units"] = detail::units_for_magnitude(magnitude);
3343  for(auto d : data) {
3344  cpptempl::data_map item;
3345  item["name"] = escape(d.first);
3346  for(auto e : d.second) {
3347  item["times"].push_back(truncate(e.count() * magnitude));
3348  }
3349 
3350  map["benchmarks"].push_back(item);
3351  }
3352 
3353  cpptempl::parse(report_stream(), templ, map);
3354 
3355  report_stream() << std::flush;
3356 
3357  if(verbose) progress_stream() << "done\n";
3358  }
3359 
3360  static double truncate(double x) {
3361  return int(x * 1000.) / 1000.;
3362  }
3363 
3364  double ideal_magnitude() const {
3365  std::vector<fp_seconds> mins;
3366  mins.reserve(data.size());
3367  for(auto d : data) {
3368  mins.push_back(*std::min_element(d.second.begin(), d.second.end()));
3369  }
3370  auto min = *std::min_element(mins.begin(), mins.end());
3371  return detail::get_magnitude(min);
3372  }
3373 
3374  static std::string escape(std::string const& source) {
3375  static const std::unordered_map<char, std::string> escapes {
3376  { '\'', "&apos;" },
3377  { '"', "&quot;" },
3378  { '<', "&lt;" },
3379  { '>', "&gt;" },
3380  { '&', "&amp;" },
3381  { '\\', "\\\\" },
3382  };
3383  return detail::escape(source, escapes);
3384  }

3446 // mismatch algorithm
3447 
3448 #define NONIUS_DETAIL_MISMATCH_HPP
3449 
3450 #include <utility>
3451 
3452 namespace nonius {
3453  namespace detail {
3454  template <typename InputIt1, typename InputIt2, typename BinaryPredicate>
3455  std::pair<InputIt1, InputIt2> mismatch(InputIt1 first1, InputIt1 last1, InputIt2 first2, InputIt2 last2, BinaryPredicate p) {
3456  while(first1 != last1 && first2 != last2 && p(*first1, *first2)) {
3457  ++first1, ++first2;
3458  }
3459  return std::make_pair(first1, first2);
3460  }
3461  } // namespace detail
3462 } // namespace nonius

3464 #include <string>
3465 #include <unordered_map>
3466 #include <vector>

3468 #include <ostream>
3469 #include <iomanip>
3470 #include <tuple>

3473 namespace nonius {
3474  namespace detail {
3475  struct option {
3476  bool matches_short(std::string const& s) const {
3477  return s == ("-" + short_form);
3478  }
3479  std::tuple<bool, std::string::const_iterator> long_separator(std::string const& s) const {
3480  auto l = "--" + long_form;
3481  auto its = detail::mismatch(s.begin(), s.end(), l.begin(), l.end(), [](char a, char b) { return a == b; });
3482  return std::make_tuple(its.second == l.end(), its.first);
3483  }
3484  bool matches_long(std::string const& s) const {
3485  return std::get<0>(long_separator(s));
3486  }
3487  bool matches_long(std::string const& s, std::string& argument) const {
3488  bool match; std::string::const_iterator it;
3489  std::tie(match, it) = long_separator(s);
3490  if(match && it != s.end()) {
3491  if(*it == '=') argument.assign(it+1, s.end());
3492  else return false;
3493  }
3494  return match;
3495  }
3496 
3497  option(std::string long_form, std::string short_form, std::string description, std::string argument = std::string(), bool multiple = false)
3498  : long_form(std::move(long_form)), short_form(std::move(short_form)), description(std::move(description)), argument(std::move(argument)), multiple(multiple) {}
3499 
3500  std::string long_form;
3501  std::string short_form;
3502  std::string description;
3503  std::string argument;
3504  bool multiple;
3505  };
3506 
3507  using option_set = std::vector<option>;
3508 
3509  struct help_text {
3510  help_text(std::string name, option_set const& options) : name(std::move(name)), options(options) {}
3511  std::string name;
3512  option_set const& options;
3513  };
3514 
3515  template <typename Iterator, typename Projection>
3516  int get_max_width(Iterator first, Iterator last, Projection proj) {
3517  auto it = std::max_element(first, last, [&proj](option const& a, option const& b) { return proj(a) < proj(b); });
3518  return static_cast<int>(proj(*it));
3519  }
3520 
3521  inline std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, help_text h) {
3522  os << "Usage: " << h.name << " [OPTIONS]\n\n";
3523 
3524  auto lwidth = 2 + get_max_width(h.options.begin(), h.options.end(), [](option const& o) { return 2 + o.long_form.size() + 1 + o.argument.size(); });
3525  auto swidth = 2 + get_max_width(h.options.begin(), h.options.end(), [](option const& o) { return 1 + o.short_form.size() + 1 + o.argument.size(); });
3526 
3527  os << std::left;
3528  for(auto o : h.options) {
3529  auto l = "--" + o.long_form;
3530  auto s = "-" + o.short_form;
3531  if(!o.argument.empty()) {
3532  l += "=" + o.argument;
3533  s += " " + o.argument;
3534  }
3535  os << std::setw(lwidth) << l
3536  << std::setw(swidth) << s
3537  << o.description
3538  << '\n';
3539  }
3540  return os;
3541  }
3542 
3543  using arguments = std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string>;
3544 
3545  struct argument_error {
3546  virtual ~argument_error() = default;
3547  };
3548 
3549  template <typename Iterator>
3550  void parse_short(option const& o, arguments& args, Iterator& first, Iterator last) {
3551  if(!o.argument.empty()) {
3552  if(++first != last) {
3553  args.emplace(o.long_form, *first);
3554  } else {
3555  throw argument_error();
3556  }
3557  } else {
3558  args.emplace(o.long_form, "");
3559  }
3560  }
3561  inline void parse_long(option const& o, arguments& args, std::string&& arg) {
3562  args.emplace(o.long_form, std::move(arg));
3563  }
3564 
3565  template <typename Iterator>
3566  arguments parse_arguments(option_set const& options, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
3567  arguments args;
3568  for(; first != last; ++first) {
3569  bool parsed = false;
3570  for(auto&& option : options) {
3571  if(option.matches_short(*first)) {
3572  parse_short(option, args, first, last);
3573  parsed = true;
3574  break;
3575  } else {
3576  std::string arg;
3577  if(option.matches_long(*first, arg)) {
3578  parse_long(option, args, std::move(arg));
3579  parsed = true;
3580  break;
3581  }
3582  }
3583  }
3584  if(!parsed) {
3585  throw argument_error();
3586  }
3587  }
3588  return args;
3589  }
3590  } // namespace detail
3591 } // namespace nonius

3593 #include <vector>
3594 #include <string>

3601 namespace nonius {
3602  namespace detail {
3603  template <typename T>
3604  struct parser;
3605  template <>
3606  struct parser<int> {
3607  static int parse(std::string const& s) { return std::stoi(s); }
3608  };
3609  template <>
3610  struct parser<double> {
3611  static double parse(std::string const& s) { return std::stod(s); }
3612  };
3613  template <>
3614  struct parser<std::string> {
3615  static std::string parse(std::string const& s) { return s; }
3616  };
3617  template <>
3618  struct parser<bool> {
3619  static bool parse(std::string const&) { return true; }
3620  };
3621  template <typename T, typename Predicate>
3622  void parse(T& variable, detail::arguments& args, std::string const& option, Predicate&& is_valid) {
3623  auto it = args.find(option);
3624  if(it != args.end()) {
3625  auto value = parser<T>::parse(it->second);
3626  if(is_valid(value)) {
3627  variable = value;
3628  } else {
3629  throw argument_error();
3630  }
3631  }
3632  }
3633  template <typename T>
3634  void parse(T& variable, detail::arguments& args, std::string const& option) {
3635  return parse(variable, args, option, [](T const&) { return true; });
3636  }

3638  inline detail::option_set const& command_line_options() {
3639  static detail::option_set the_options {
3640  detail::option("help", "h", "show this help message"),
3641  detail::option("samples", "s", "number of samples to collect (default: 100)", "SAMPLES"),
3642  detail::option("resamples", "rs", "number of resamples for the bootstrap (default: 100000)", "RESAMPLES"),
3643  detail::option("confidence-interval", "ci", "confidence interval for the bootstrap (between 0 and 1, default: 0.95)", "INTERVAL"),
3644  detail::option("output", "o", "output file (default: <stdout>)", "FILE"),
3645  detail::option("reporter", "r", "reporter to use (default: standard)", "REPORTER"),
3646  detail::option("title", "t", "set report title", "TITLE"),
3647  detail::option("no-analysis", "A", "perform only measurements; do not perform any analysis"),
3648  detail::option("list", "l", "list benchmarks"),
3649  detail::option("list-reporters", "lr", "list available reporters"),
3650  detail::option("verbose", "v", "show verbose output (mutually exclusive with -q)"),
3651  detail::option("summary", "q", "show summary output (mutually exclusive with -v)"),
3652  };
3653  return the_options;
3654  }
3655 
3656  template <typename Iterator>
3657  configuration parse_args(std::string const& name, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
3658  try {
3659  auto args = detail::parse_arguments(command_line_options(), first, last);
3660 
3661  configuration cfg;
3662 
3663  auto is_positive = [](int x) { return x > 0; };
3664  auto is_ci = [](double x) { return x > 0 && x < 1; };
3665  auto is_reporter = [](std::string const x) { return global_reporter_registry().count(x) > 0; };
3666 
3667  parse(cfg.help, args, "help");
3668  parse(cfg.samples, args, "samples", is_positive);
3669  parse(cfg.resamples, args, "resamples", is_positive);
3670  parse(cfg.confidence_interval, args, "confidence-interval", is_ci);
3671  parse(cfg.output_file, args, "output");
3672  parse(cfg.reporter, args, "reporter", is_reporter);
3673  parse(cfg.no_analysis, args, "no-analysis");
3674  parse(cfg.list_benchmarks, args, "list");
3675  parse(cfg.list_reporters, args, "list-reporters");
3676  parse(cfg.verbose, args, "verbose");
3677  parse(cfg.summary, args, "summary");
3678  parse(cfg.title, args, "title");
3679  if(cfg.verbose && cfg.summary) throw argument_error();
3680 
3681  return cfg;
3682  } catch(...) {
3683  std::cout << help_text(name, command_line_options());
3684  throw argument_error();
3685  }
3686  }
3687  } // namespace detail
3688 
3689  inline int print_help(std::string const& name) {
3690  std::cout << detail::help_text(name, detail::command_line_options());
3691  return 0;
3692  }
3693  inline int list_benchmarks() {
3694  std::cout << "All available benchmarks:\n";
3695  for(auto&& b : global_benchmark_registry()) {
3696  std::cout << " " << b.name << "\n";
3697  }
3698  std::cout << global_benchmark_registry().size() << " benchmarks\n\n";
3699  return 0;
3700  }
3701  inline int list_reporters() {
3702  using reporter_entry_ref = decltype(*global_reporter_registry().begin());
3703  auto cmp = [](reporter_entry_ref a, reporter_entry_ref b) { return a.first.size() < b.first.size(); };
3704  auto width = 2 + std::max_element(global_reporter_registry().begin(), global_reporter_registry().end(), cmp)->first.size();
3705 
3706  std::cout << "Available reporters:\n";
3707  std::cout << std::left;
3708  for(auto&& r : global_reporter_registry()) {
3709  if(!r.first.empty()) {
3710  std::cout << " " << std::setw(width) << r.first << r.second->description() << "\n";
3711  }
3712  }
3713  std::cout << '\n';
3714  return 0;
3715  }
3716  inline int run_it(configuration cfg) {
3717  try {
3718  nonius::go(cfg);
3719  } catch(...) {
3720  std::cerr << "PANIC: clock is on fire\n";
3721  try {
3722  throw;
3723  } catch(std::exception const& e) {
3724  std::cerr << " " << e.what() << "\n";
3725  } catch(...) {}
3726  return 23;
3727  }
3728  return 0;
3729  }
3730 
3731  template <typename Iterator>
3732  int main(std::string const& name, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
3733  configuration cfg;
3734 
3735  try {
3736  cfg = detail::parse_args(name, first, last);
3737  } catch(detail::argument_error const&) {
3738  return 17;
3739  }
3740 
3741  if(cfg.help) return print_help(name);
3742  else if(cfg.list_benchmarks) return list_benchmarks();
3743  else if(cfg.list_reporters) return list_reporters();
3744  else return run_it(cfg);
3745  }
3746  inline int main(int argc, char** argv) {
3747  std::string name(argv[0]);
3748  std::vector<std::string> args(argv+1, argv+argc);
3749  return main(name, args.begin(), args.end());
3750  }
3751 }
